      </A_Z_spin>
      <Isomeric_yields>
--------------------------------------------
--- Relative independent isomeric yields ---
--------------------------------------------
 
The calculation is based on spin and energy values from JEFF-3.3.
 
J and E* are the spin and the excitation energy of the state.
Yield is the relative production yield of that state.
The number of events allows to estimate the statistical uncertainty.
The 'upper limit' is an internal parameter to calculate the yield.
 
The listed yield values only include the first population
of the state (ground state or one of the isomeric states)
by the emission of 'prompt' neutrons and gammas.
Note that measured yields may include the population
by the delayed consecutive decay from higher-lying isomers,
depending on the conditions of the experiment!
 
